e, number of classes, height, width)\r\n- compare it with a target of dimension (batch size, height, width)\r\n\r\nSo i wanted to use Catalyst's metrics, such as AccuracyCallback, but it seems like it only support tensor of this size :\r\n- targets is a tensor: batch_size\r\n- outputs is a tensor: batch_size x num_classes\r\n\r\nBecause of that, it pass the multi label condition, in catalyst/utils/metrics/accuracy.py\r\n`# multi-label classification`\r\n`if len(targets.shape) > 1 and targets.size(1) > 1:`\r\n`output = (targets.long() == outputs.long()).sum().float() / np.prod(targets.shape)`\r\n`return [output]`\r\nand i get this error\r\n`RuntimeError: The size of tensor a (4) must match the size of tensor b (2) at non-singleton dimension 1`\r\n\r\nIs there a way to make it work nevertheless ? ","closed_by":{"login":"le-Greg","id":68744272,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4NzQ0Mjcy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/68744272?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg","html_url":"https://github.com/le-Greg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/le-Greg/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catalyst-team/catalyst/issues/896/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/catalyst-team/catalyst/issues/896/timeline","perfo